<section id="Section949448">
  <title>
      <anchor id="Anchor952510" role="Index" xreflabel="comment types:master list of"/> 
      <indexterm significance="normal">
         <primary>comment types</primary>

         <secondary>creating new</secondary>
      </indexterm>Comment Type</title>

  <para id="Para952472">To create a new Comment Type, select the NEW button.
  The following screen will appear:</para>

  <para id="Para952476">
      <screenshot>
         <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
               <imagedata fileref="images/Sys_commTypeNew.png" id="Graphic952474"/>
            </imageobject>

            <caption id="Caption952478">Create New Comment Type</caption>
         </mediaobject>
      </screenshot>
   </para>

  <para id="Para952479">When creating a new Comment Type, you are presented
  with the following options:</para>

  <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
         <term id="Para952567">Name</term>

         <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1879fa0">
            <para>Enter a unique Comment Type name.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
         <term id="Para952572">Description</term>

         <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1879fe8">
            <para>Enter a brief description of the Comment Type.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <para id="Para952574">To the far right of the screen, the following buttons
  are available:</para>

  <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
         <term id="Para952575">CANCEL</term>

         <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x187a054">
            <para>Closes the screen without adding a new Comment Type to the
        master list of Comment Types.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
         <term id="Para952576">SAVE</term>

         <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x187a09c">
            <para>Creates the Comment Type and adds it to the master list of
        Comment Types.</para>
         </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>